HEADWORD: Hospice
<hw>Hos"pice</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. L.
<ets>hospitium</ets> hospitality, a place where strangers are
entertained, fr. <ets>hospes</ets> stranger, guest. See <er>Host</er> a
landlord.]</ety> <def>A convent or monastery which is also a place of
refuge or entertainment for travelers on some difficult road or pass, as
in the Alps; <as>as, the <ex>Hospice</ex> of the Great St</as>.
Bernard.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hospitable</ent>⟦br⟧
